<subSubSection pageId="33" pageNumber="34" type="type">
<paragraph pageId="33" pageNumber="34">Type:</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="33" pageNumber="34">
Mexico, Chihuahua, Municipio de Guadalupe y Calvo, Sierra Madre Occidental, N side of Cerro Mohinora, ca. 13 mi SW of Guadalupe y Calvo, open pine-fir woods with scattered spruce, nearly vertical, N facing rock wall, very moist with many bryophytes and rich herbaceous flora, 
<geoCoordinate degrees="25" direction="north" minutes="57" orientation="latitude" precision="925" value="25.95">25°57'N</geoCoordinate>
, 
<geoCoordinate degrees="107" direction="west" minutes="03" orientation="longitude" precision="925" value="-107.05">107°03'W</geoCoordinate>
, 2950 m, 20 Aug 1988, 
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="33" pageNumber="34">G.Nesom &amp; A.McDonald 6475</emphasis>
(holotype: TEX!; isotype: ARIZ!).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="33" pageNumber="34" type="description">
<paragraph pageId="33" pageNumber="34">Description.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="33" pageNumber="34">
<emphasis bold="true" pageId="33" pageNumber="34">Leaf</emphasis>
sheaths retrorsely scabrous to puberulent; collars ciliate; ligules abaxially puberulent. 
<emphasis bold="true" pageId="33" pageNumber="34">Lemma</emphasis>
keel and marginal veins proximally puberulent, between veins densely scabrous. 
<emphasis bold="true" pageId="33" pageNumber="34">Lodicules</emphasis>
0.75 mm long, broadly ovate with a broad lateral lobe.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="33" pageNumber="34" type="distribution">
<paragraph pageId="33" pageNumber="34">Distribution.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="33" pageNumber="34">This subspecies is known only from the Sierra Mohinora, Chihuahua.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection lastPageId="34" lastPageNumber="35" pageId="33" pageNumber="34" type="ecology">
<paragraph pageId="33" pageNumber="34">Ecology.</paragraph>
<paragraph lastPageId="34" lastPageNumber="35" pageId="33" pageNumber="34">
