<subSubSection pageId="34" pageNumber="35" type="discussion">
<paragraph pageId="34" pageNumber="35">Discussion.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="34" pageNumber="35">
When the second author visited the type locality in 2006, the habitat within 5 km of the peak was found to be quite disturbed by grazing and logging. The holotype was initially determined as 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Vasey" authorityYear="1888" class="Liliopsida" family="Poaceae" genus="Poa" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="" order="Poales" pageId="34" pageNumber="35" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="tracyi">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="34" pageNumber="35">Poa tracyi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
&quot;vel. aff.&quot; by J.R &amp; C.G. Reeder in 1989).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
